  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e96c934f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Multicollinearity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "882d0481",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-04-08T19:46:59.673833Z",
     "start_time": "2026-04-08T19:46:59.529598Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "# Select only numerical columns\n",
    "numeric_clinical_df = clinical_df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute correlation matrix\n",
    "corr_matrix = numeric_clinical_df.corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mask upper triangle for cleaner heatmap\n",
    "mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr_matrix, dtype=bool))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot heatmap\n",
    "sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, mask=mask, cmap='coolwarm', annot=False)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Collinearity (Correlation) Matrix - Numerical Columns\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# List highly collinear numerical features\n",
    "threshold = 0.7\n",
    "high_corr = np.where((corr_matrix.abs() > threshold) & (corr_matrix.abs() < 1))\n",
    "high_corr_pairs = [(corr_matrix.index[x], corr_matrix.columns[y]) for x, y in zip(*high_corr)]\n",
    "print(\"Highly collinear numerical feature pairs (>|0.7|):\")\n",
    "print(high_corr_pairs)"
   ],
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ],
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Highly collinear numerical feature pairs (>|0.7|):\n",
      "[('neoplasm_histologic_grade', 'nottingham_prognostic_index'), ('nottingham_prognostic_index', 'neoplasm_histologic_grade')]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 36
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0c23f9d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that there is only one pair of columns that exceed a correlation of 0.7,`neoplasm_histologic_grade` and `nottingham_prognostic_index`. `neoplasm_histologic_grade` refers to a tumor grade that describes how abnormal the cancer cells look under a microscope (a measure of aggressiveness). `nottingham_prognostic_index` is a derived column that predicts overall prognosis.\n",
    "\n",
    "For survival analysis, we do not want to use `nottingham_prognostic_index`, because it is essentially a tool to predict survival, so before the models are made, this column will be dropped in favor of `neoplasm_histologic_grade`. But for illustration and analysis purposes, we will temporarily keep both."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e13eff89",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Survival Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a55057a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note: for the survival curve, we need to note the proportion of people in each category, because a 100% survival rate in a strata is not impressive if the proportion of people who are alive and in the strata is small.\n",
    "\n",
    "In this analysis, the goal was to assess the impact of various treatments on patient survival, considering the potential confounding factors such as tumor stage, cancer type, and the presence of aggressive treatments like chemotherapy, radiotherapy, and hormone therapy.  We focused on stratifying the Kaplan-Meier survival curves by tumor stage and treatment types, which were chemotherapy, radiotherapy, and hormone therapy.\n",
    "\n",
    "After performing exploratory data analysis (EDA) and addressing multicollinearity, the goal was observe the surival curves of patients with specific characteristics within the METABRIC study: the impact of tumor stage, cancer type, and various treatments on patient survival."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "93c4bcb0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Kaplan-Meier Curves: Stratified Comparisans"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "798aa72c",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-04-08T19:47:10.935904Z",
     "start_time": "2026-04-08T19:47:10.923465Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "time_to_event = clinical_df['overall_survival_months']\n",
    "event = clinical_df['event_observed']\n",
    "\n",
    "kmf = KaplanMeierFitter()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "375d25b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### a. Tumor Stage"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "id": "98ffb0c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))\n",
    "\n",
    "ctype_fits = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for ctype in clinical_df['tumor_stage'].dropna().unique():\n",
    "    mask = clinical_df['tumor_stage'] == ctype\n",
    "    kmf.fit(clinical_df['overall_survival_months'][mask], \n",
    "            event_observed=clinical_df['event_observed'][mask], \n",
    "            label=ctype)\n",
    "    ax = kmf.plot_survival_function(ci_show=True, show_censors=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ctype_fits.append(KaplanMeierFitter().fit(\n",
    "        clinical_df['overall_survival_months'][mask],\n",
    "        event_observed=clinical_df['event_observed'][mask],\n",
    "        label=ctype\n",
    "    ))\n",
    "\n",
    "add_at_risk_counts(*ctype_fits, ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Kaplan–Meier Curves by Tumor Stage\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Months\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Survival Probability\")\n",
    "plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05,1))\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
